<subSubSection type="description">
<paragraph box="[249,1159,366,736]" pageId="23" pageNumber="276" type="mainText">
Annual plants or subshrubs. Leaves alternate, fleshy. Flowers bisexual or pistillate, in 3-27-flowered clusters; perianth free almost to the base, all or some segments winged, membranous or coriaceous; stamens 2-5, split to the midst, unappendaged or with a small, obtuse appendage; disk with glandular lobes; stigmas 2. Nine spp., W and C Asia, N Africa. 
<taxonomicName authority="Bunge, 1862 (Fenzl)" authorityName="Bunge, 1862 (Fenzl)" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Amaranthaceae" genus="Agathophora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="23" pageNumber="276" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus" subGenus="Agathophora">Agathophora</taxonomicName>
is often considered to represent a separate genus.
</paragraph>
